{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "04", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "20", "M": "11", "S": "15"}}, "news": [{"title": "Lucknow development body extends deadline for Atal Nagar housing scheme", "para": "The Lucknow Development Authority has extended the registration deadline for its Atal Nagar Housing Scheme to November 21, offering 2,496 1-BHK and 2-BHK flats for low and middle-income groups. Meanwhile, the Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel Housing Scheme in Dalibagh, featuring 72 flats on land recovered from illegal possession, saw an overwhelming response and concluded its registration on November 3.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/lucknow-development-authority-extends-atal-nagar-housing-scheme-registration-deadline-to-november-21/125074127?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-262948/125074127.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Noida airport nearly ready but survey finds 94% business plots along Yamuna expressway unused", "para": "A government survey reveals a significant portion of industrial land along the Yamuna Expressway remains undeveloped, with 94% of plots vacant just months before the Noida International Airport's launch. This contrasts sharply with Noida's robust industrial occupancy, highlighting stalled growth potential in the YEIDA region despite rising demand.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/noida-airport-set-to-launch-amidst-unused-industrial-land-crisis/125073898?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-189632/125073898.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Gujarat plans five new satellite towns to ease urban expansion", "para": "Gujarat's government is transforming five towns\u2014Kalol, Sanand, Savli, Bardoli, and Hirasar\u2014into fully developed satellite towns around its major cities. A high-level committee will oversee infrastructure development to ensure synchronized growth, aiming to ease pressure on urban centers and foster balanced development and investment.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/gujarat-unveils-ambitious-plans-for-five-new-satellite-towns-to-support-urban-growth/125073703?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-54542/125073703.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}